TABLE 7 
Top-1 accuracy under the linear evaluation on ImageNet with the 
ResNet-50 backbone. ReSSL with * denote the results without 
predictor and InfoNCE warm-up.

Table 7. 
For a fair comparison, we divide previous methods into 
1x backprop and 2x backprop settings since 2x backprop 
methods generally require more GPU memories and longer 
training. As we can see clearly that ReSSL consistently out-
performs previous methods on both setting. For 1x setting, 
ReSSL surpass previous state-of-the-art (InfoMin) 1.9%. For 
2x setting, ReSSL has 0.4% improvements over MoCo v3 
with only 2/3 training costs and smaller batch size. We also 
report the performance when working without the predictor 
and InfoNCE warm-up. In this case, the performance drops 
2.1% and 1.8% for 1x and 2x setting, respectively, which 
further verified the effectiveness of these two strategies.
